Method: shape_collide(shape_rid: RID, transform: Transform3D, motion: Vector3, exclude: Array[RID] = [], collision_mask: int = 4294967295, collide_with_bodies: bool = true, collide_with_areas: bool = false) → Array[Dictionary]
  Performs a shape collision query, returning all shapes that would collide with the given shape during its motion.

  Parameters:
  - shape_rid (RID): The RID of the shape to collide.
  - transform (Transform3D): The initial transform of the shape.
  - motion (Vector3): The motion vector of the shape.
  - exclude (Array[RID]): An array of RIDs to exclude from the collision check.
  - collision_mask (int): A bitmask specifying which collision layers to check against. Defaults to all layers.
  - collide_with_bodies (bool): Whether to check for collisions with physics bodies.
  - collide_with_areas (bool): Whether to check for collisions with physics areas.

  Returns: An array of dictionaries, each containing collision information for a colliding shape.

