Document: PhysicsDirectSpaceState3D
Path: godot/classes/class_physicsdirectspacestate3d.rst
Summary: Provides access to the physics space state for direct manipulation and queries.

Inherits: Object

Methods:
Method: intersect_ray(from: Vector3, to: Vector3, exclude: Array[RID] = [], collision_mask: int = 1, collide_with_bodies: bool = true, collide_with_shapes: bool = true) → Dictionary
  Performs a raycast query in the physics space. Returns a dictionary with intersection details if a hit occurs, otherwise an empty dictionary.

Method: intersect_shape(shape_rid: RID, shape_xform: Transform3D, motion: Vector3, shape_type: int = 0, max_results: int = 0, exclude: Array[RID] = [], collision_mask: int = 1, collide_with_bodies: bool = true, collide_with_shapes: bool = true) → Array[Dictionary]
  Performs a shape intersection query. Returns an array of dictionaries, each containing intersection details.

Method: cast_motion(from: Transform3D, motion: Vector3, shape_rid: RID, shape_xform: Transform3D, max_results: int = 0, exclude: Array[RID] = [], collision_mask: int = 1, collide_with_bodies: bool = true, collide_with_shapes: bool = true) → Array[Dictionary]
  Casts a shape through the physics space to determine the motion it can travel before colliding. Returns an array of dictionaries with collision information.

Method: collide_shape(shape_rid: RID, shape_xform: Transform3D, motion: Vector3, shape_type: int = 0, exclude: Array[RID] = [], collision_mask: int = 1, collide_with_bodies: bool = true, collide_with_shapes: bool = true) → Dictionary
  Calculates the collision point and normal for a shape moving through the physics space. Returns a dictionary with collision details.

Method: collide_and_slide(shape_rid: RID, shape_xform: Transform3D, motion: Vector3, shape_type: int = 0, exclude: Array[RID] = [], collision_mask: int = 1, collide_with_bodies: bool = true, collide_with_shapes: bool = true) → Array[Dictionary]
  Simulates a shape colliding and sliding along surfaces in the physics space. Returns an array of dictionaries describing the collisions.

Method: body_test_motion(body_rid: RID, body_xform: Transform3D, motion: Vector3, shape_idx: int = -1, exclude: Array[RID] = [], collision_mask: int = 1, collide_with_bodies: bool = true, collide_with_shapes: bool = true) → Dictionary
  Tests the motion of a specific physics body. Returns a dictionary with collision details if a collision occurs.

Method: body_get_shape_by_point(body_rid: RID, point: Vector3) → int
  Retrieves the index of the shape on a physics body that contains the given point.

Method: body_get_shape_by_normal(body_rid: RID, normal: Vector3) → int
  Retrieves the index of the shape on a physics body that is facing the given normal.

Method: body_get_shape_by_segment(body_rid: RID, from: Vector3, to: Vector3) → int
  Retrieves the index of the shape on a physics body that intersects the given segment.

Method: body_get_shape_by_aabb(body_rid: RID, aabb: AABB) → int
  Retrieves the index of the shape on a physics body that intersects the given AABB.

Method: body_get_shape_by_radius(body_rid: RID, point: Vector3, radius: float) → int
  Retrieves the index of the shape on a physics body that is within the given radius of the point.

Method: body_get_shape_by_radius_normal(body_rid: RID, point: Vector3, radius: float, normal: Vector3) → int
  Retrieves the index of the shape on a physics body that is within the given radius of the point and facing the given normal.

Method: body_get_shape_by_radius_segment(body_rid: RID, from: Vector3, to: Vector3, radius: float) → int
